<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-584-824  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 584 824.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  June 25 1990 n306 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>24-hour trading effort.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schwartz, Jeffrey.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Chicago Board Options Exchange (CBOE), American Stock Exchangeand Cincinnati Stock Exchange have formed a partnership withReuters Holding PLC to develop an electronic system for overnightglobal trading.andP;  Reuters will provide the terminals and networkthat will interface with the host and CBOE will operate thesystem's host computer.andP;  The system will not be operational before1992; the stock exchanges are currently developing specificationsfor a routing platform and host computer.andP;  The network will bebased on the Globex automated futures trading system.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Chicago Board Options Exchange (contracts)Reuters Holdings PLC (contracts)American Stock Exchange (contracts)Cincinnati Stock Exchange (contracts).andO;Topic:     Financial TerminalsElectronic Trading SystemsStock MarketContractsNetwork ArchitecturePartnership.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>